description:
Associate Director, Professional Program (Tax Education)





Chartered Professional Accountants of Canada (CPA Canada) represents the Canadian accounting profession, both nationally and internationally. Operating in the highly complex and global accounting eco-system, CPA Canada is a convener, facilitator, contributor and disseminator of information that advances the profession. The organization works closely with the provincial, territorial and Bermudan CPA bodies to champion best practices that benefit business and society. With more than 217,000 members, CPA Canada is one of the largest national accounting bodies in the world. The organization supports the setting of accounting, auditing and assurance standards, advocates for economic and social development in the public interest, and develops leading-edge thought leadership, research, guidance and educational programs. cpacanada.ca 





About the opportunity


The Professional Programs team is focused on serving customers' needs for ongoing professional development. Ongoing education helps them advance in their careers, create value for their clients, and succeed in their communities. Using market needs analysis and research assessment developed by the Business Development team, members of this team work with subject matter experts and advisory committees to develop conferences, online and blended learnings such as certificates, virtual classrooms and podcasts, and other opportunities to help members continually upgrade their professional and leadership skills. 

As an Associate Director, Professional Program (Tax Education) at CPA Canada, you will work in close collaboration with other members of the Tax group and, where appropriate, across CPA Canada and with our provincial partners. You will ensure the delivery of products and services, including CPA Canada’s In-Depth Tax program, that support members in the business communities they serve. You will be responsible for anticipating and producing professional development programs, services and many of CPA Canada’s leading publications to the financial business community. 





What you’ll do In this role you will: 


• Lead the business planning process and product development projects to ensure the financial and business objectives are met; 

• Make strategic decisions regarding the delivery and the content of the In-Depth Tax Program using stakeholder’s inputs; 

• Responsible for the ongoing team leadership to ensure a highly performing team that delivers on its objectives; 

• Work closely with Tax Principals and Program Managers to ensure programs are executed in an efficient manner; 

• Identify products, coordinate development and ensure relevant professional development is produced for members to support their careers; 

• Work closely with subject matter experts, marketing team, external partners and other CPA departments to ensure commercial success of products; 

• Develop partnerships with stakeholders who have complementary interests within the product portfolio; 

• Collaborate with colleagues in other operating groups across CPA Canada; 

• Develop relationships and strategic partnerships with key stakeholders and organizational leaders in various public and private organizations. 

• Manage and participate in various advisory committees, to engage appropriate stakeholders in the development and ongoing assessment of CPA Canada’s strategy and the delivery of value-add products. 

• Support the technical review process of content and work closely with the Learning Design &amp; Development team to assess and determine the most appropriate format for delivering products and bring innovative new delivery formats for our customers 






The ideal candidate will have the following skills and experience: 


• CPA designation is required 

• Teaching experience or knowledge of adult learning is an asset 

• Minimum of 5-10 years of post-designation experience in taxation 

• Minimum of 5 years of experience managing and leading a team 

• Completion of CPA Canada’s In-Depth Tax Program 

• Working knowledge of GST/HST; 

• Knowledge of recent and emerging trends in the profession 

• Knowledgeable about CPA practices and sufficiently adaptable and experienced to undertake various senior level tasks as required; 

• Understanding and awareness of drivers that could impact business; 

• Strong technical aptitude 

• Ability to prioritize multiple projects and set clear directions 

• Strong interpersonal skills (including client management) with ability to liaise effectively with senior members of the CPA profession and other external stakeholders, including government, accounting firms, other professional associations etc. 

• Must have excellent English written and oral communication skills and be able to speak comfortably to a variety of audiences including strong facilitation, presentation and public speaking skills. 

• Excellent strategic, analytical and conceptual thinking skills and ability to identify needs and initiate, coordinate and manage the implementation of creative solutions. 

• Ability to work with limited supervision and to respond quickly to changing demands and new issues; 

• Intellectual curiosity and keen desire to learn; 

• Must be open to travel to off-site locations as required 





What it’s like to work here


With a diverse workforce and a commitment to health and wellness for its employees, CPA Canada is a great place to work. The organization offers a flexible and balanced environment that allows individuals to maximize professional and personal development. CPA Canada employs over 400 people, with its headquarters in Toronto and other offices in Burnaby, Ottawa and Montreal. Our technology-enabled culture is designed to attract qualified people and enable them to do their best work. Employee perks include competitive salaries and pension, a comprehensive benefits package, professional development programs, flexible working hours and opportunities to work from home, regular social events and a highly successful employee volunteer program. In addition, CPA Canada is dedicated to continual improvement and building a high-performing, innovative organization that creates value for members and other stakeholders. 





Organization values 


We create a collaborative and constructive culture by: • Acting with Integrity • Fostering Excellence • Respecting Others • Working Collaboratively • Being Accountable CPA Canada is committed to cultivating and inclusive, accessible environment, where each employee feels respected, valued and supported. All qualified individuals may apply online. If you require a disability related accommodation to participate in our recruitment process, please make a note of this in your application and we’ll be happy to work with you to meet your needs 





COVID-19 Vaccination Policy


CPA Canada is committed to the health and safety of our people, our stakeholders, and the communities where we live and work. Accordingly, all CPA Canada employees must be fully vaccinated as a condition of employment per our Vaccination Policy. Therefore, CPA Canada will make the successful candidate an offer of employment on the condition of being fully vaccinated against COVID-19 and providing proof of vaccination before their start date. “Fully vaccinated” is defined as having received the complete series of an accepted COVID-19 vaccine, or any combination thereof, at least 14 days before the employment start date, as stipulated by the Ministry of Health and Public Health authorities in the respective jurisdiction of hire. 




If the candidate has a documented exemption that may be protected by Human Rights legislation in the respective jurisdiction of hire, a request for accommodation may be sought prior to the employment start date by furnishing written proof that is accepted and deemed satisfactory to CPA Canada.

We are currently seeking a temporary In-House Paralegal to join our global Legal &amp; Compliance team. This is a one-year contract role that reports into the Director, Legal &amp; Compliance. The successful incumbent will provide support for various types of corporate transactions, corporate governance, compliance, contracting and intellectual property matters. If you are enthusiastic, driven, and keen to apply your current experience with a yearning to expand your knowledge and skills, we want to hear from you!




This position is located at the Hexagon Campus in Calgary, Alberta which opened in September 2018. In this state-of-the-art location, we offer a casual and innovative work environment, including leading edge technology, on-site gymnasium, dedicated bike storage room, and underground parking.




As our 
In-House Paralegal
 you will be responsible for providing authoritative and comprehensive paralegal services meeting the commercial and strategic needs of the business. Specifically, you will:

· Maintain the corporate minute books and prepare and file annual returns and consent resolutions;

· File director and officer changes and keep various internal corporate databases up to date;

· Maintain the Legal &amp; Compliance department's document filing system, and be responsible for document and form management;

· Prepare, draft and send standard form documents and templates;

· Coordinate execution of contracts and corporate resolutions.

· Manage the Intellectual Property files and registers;

· Assist with special projects and training as assigned, including but not limited to acting as a compliance lead for internal compliance initiatives, risk assessment reviews, and assistance with external customer requests;

· Maintain current knowledge of internal policies and procedures relative to legal and regulatory requirements;

· Conduct research as assigned;

· Perform such other tasks which the Director, Legal &amp; Compliance may require you to undertake from time to time.






Qualifications:







Must Have:


· 3-7 years of relevant experience in business, IP and/or regulatory law acquired at a large firm or multinational company;

· Graduate of a post-secondary, accredited Paralegal program;

· Capacity to manage many files simultaneously, work well under pressure and exercise initiative;

· Excellent written and oral communication skills;

· Capacity to occasionally accommodate a flexible schedule;

· Exceptional time management skills, with the ability to meet deadlines and manage competing priorities, whilst working in a fast-paced environment;

· Ability to work independently with minimal supervision.





Key Success Factors:


· Excellent analytical skills, good judgment, organizational skills and high attention to detail;

· Client-service oriented, including strong interpersonal and relationship building skills;

· Proactive and positive team player.





Nice to Have:


· Experience with Canadian, UK and EU privacy laws;

· Working knowledge of intellectual property global filing requirements;

· Contract management experience.
